bindings:
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Experience exploring Lan Ha Bay by kayaking combined with trekking&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; offers a perfect dual experience: paddling your own boat to weave through magical limestone caves, while challenging yourself climbing the mountains through Cat Ba National Park to take in the full panorama of the bay from the summit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Why should you try the experience of exploring Lan Ha Bay by kayaking combined with trekking once in your life?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Many travelers often ask: &quot;Why not just sit on a cruise for comfort?&quot; The answer lies in freedom. When you have the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;experience of exploring Lan Ha Bay by kayaking combined with trekking&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;, you become the master of your own journey.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;A deep connection with nature: Kayaking allows you to enter small nooks and tunnels that large boats can never reach.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Pushing your own limits: Trekking through the kim giao forests or up to Ngu Lam Peak requires endurance, helping you train both body and mind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;A one-of-a-kind photo opportunity: From the mountaintop, you will take in the entire panorama of Lan Ha Bay with tiny boats like bean pods &mdash; a perspective whose real emotion no drone can replace.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Healing the soul: The stillness of the ocean and the rustling leaves of the old forest are precious remedies that help relieve all the stress of urban life.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/0000/1/2025/12/30/kinh-nghiem-kham-pha-vinh-lan-ha-bang-kayaking-ket-hop-trekking-6.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;900&quot; height=&quot;600&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;When is the ideal time to experience this combined tour?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Weather is the key factor determining the success of the trip. According to the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;experience of exploring Lan Ha Bay by kayaking combined with trekking&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; of those who went before, you should pay attention to the following time frames:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Summer (April to June): This is the most beautiful time. The sun is brilliant, the bay water is crystal clear, and the sea is very calm. However, you need to prepare sunscreen carefully because trekking under the summer sun can be quite exhausting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Autumn (September to November): The air is cool and pleasant, very suitable for climbing without being too hot. The sea water is a bit cold at this time but still warm enough for comfortable kayaking.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Note on the storm season: From July to August there are often sudden storms. You should monitor the weather forecast continuously to avoid being stranded on the island or having the tour abruptly canceled.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/0000/1/2025/12/30/kinh-nghiem-kham-pha-vinh-lan-ha-bang-kayaking-ket-hop-trekking-2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;900&quot; height=&quot;600&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;What clothing and equipment should you prepare to ensure safety?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;To have a perfect trip, preparing personal items is extremely important. You cannot use your everyday walking shoes to climb limestone mountains or wear thick jeans when paddling.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;For the kayaking activity:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Swimwear or quick-dry sportswear: Avoid cotton fabrics because they absorb water and become heavy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Dry bag: To protect your phone, camera, and valuable items.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Wide-brimmed hat and sunglasses: Protect you from UV rays reflecting off the water surface.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Life jacket: Always wear it, even if you are an excellent swimmer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;For the trekking activity:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Hiking shoes with good grip: Cat Ba terrain is mostly very sharp and slippery limestone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Long sports trousers: Help protect your legs from scratches by thorny plants and forest insects.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Small backpack: To hold drinking water, snacks, and a personal first-aid kit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Insect spray: Cat Ba National Park has quite a lot of mosquitoes and leeches during the humid season.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/0000/1/2025/12/30/kinh-nghiem-kham-pha-vinh-lan-ha-bang-kayaking-ket-hop-trekking-4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;900&quot; height=&quot;617&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Suggested itinerary: Experience exploring Lan Ha Bay by kayaking combined with trekking, 2 days 1 night&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Below is a detailed itinerary to help you optimize your time and experience in the most systematic way:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Day 1: Master the paddle amid the wonder&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;08:00:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; Depart from Beo Wharf, board the boat and head into the center of Lan Ha Bay. Along the way, you will pass by Cai Beo fishing village &mdash; the oldest fishing village in Vietnam.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;10:00:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; Start kayaking in the Bright Cave - Dark Cave area. This is an area with a unique geological structure, with caves connecting to each other through enclosed lagoons.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;12:00:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; Enjoy a seafood lunch right on the boat or at a pristine beach such as Van Boi.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;14:00:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; Continue paddling to the Ba Trai Dao area to swim and relax.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;17:00:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; Watch the sunset over the bay. This is the most glorious moment as the fiery red sun gradually sets behind the ranges of limestone mountains.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;19:00:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; Have dinner and join in night squid fishing or listen to music amid the vast sea and sky.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Day 2: Conquer the summit and cross the old forest&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;07:00:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; Have breakfast and travel to Viet Hai fishing village &mdash; a village completely isolated from the outside world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;08:30:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; Begin the trek from Viet Hai village through Cat Ba National Park. You will pass through ancient forest canopies and hear the forest birds singing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;10:30:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; Conquer Ngu Lam Peak. From here, you will see the greatness of nature with hundreds of lush green islands standing out against the aquamarine sea.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;12:00:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; Return to the village and enjoy rustic local dishes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;15:00:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; Board the boat to return to the wharf, ending an inspiring journey of discovery.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;color:#e74c3c;background-color:#ffffff;vertical-align:baseline;&quot;&gt;In addition, discover many high-quality travel experiences at&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://vietnamtoure.com/&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;color:#e74c3c;background-color:#ffffff;vertical-align:baseline;&quot;&gt; Vietnamtoure.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/0000/1/2025/12/30/kinh-nghiem-kham-pha-vinh-lan-ha-bang-kayaking-ket-hop-trekking-3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;900&quot; height=&quot;599&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Secrets to trekking the tropical forest in Cat Ba without getting exhausted&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Trekking in the Lan Ha Bay and Cat Ba area is not as difficult as the peaks in the Northwest, but the high humidity and limestone terrain can quickly exhaust you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Keep your breathing steady: Don&#039;t walk too fast on the flat sections; save your energy for the steep climbs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Drink water in small sips: You shouldn&#039;t drink too much water at once because it will make your stomach heavy and make you thirsty faster.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Use a trekking pole: A pole will help reduce the pressure on your knees by about 20-30%, especially when going downhill.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Listen to the guide: They are people who have hands-on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;experience of exploring Lan Ha Bay by kayaking combined with trekking&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;; they know where the tree roots hold firmly and which rocks easily come loose.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/0000/1/2025/12/30/kinh-nghiem-kham-pha-vinh-lan-ha-bang-kayaking-ket-hop-trekking-1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;900&quot; height=&quot;505&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;What to eat to replenish your energy after a day of activity?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Lan Ha cuisine is a blend of the flavors of the sea and the forest. Don&#039;t miss the following specialties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Geoduck grilled with scallion oil: A famous specialty of the Cat Ba sea region, with a sweet, refreshing taste and a crunchy texture.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Salt-roasted mantis shrimp: A protein-rich dish that helps you recover your muscles quickly after trekking.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Viet Hai hill chicken: The chicken is free-ranged naturally in the forest, so the meat is very firm and fragrant.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Horseshoe crab: A unique dish, but one that needs to be prepared by experienced chefs to ensure safety.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/0000/1/2025/12/30/kinh-nghiem-kham-pha-vinh-lan-ha-bang-kayaking-ket-hop-trekking-5.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;900&quot; height=&quot;597&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;How to choose a reputable tour operator?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Nowadays there are many companies providing services in Cat Ba; however, to have a trip that is truly &quot;healing&quot; and safe, you should choose operators that have:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;A team of guides who know the local area well and hold professional rescue certifications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Equipment (kayaks, life jackets, trekking gear) that is new and up to standard.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;A commitment to sustainable tourism that does not harm the natural environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;A flexible itinerary that doesn&#039;t cram too many destinations into a short time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Virenaretreat&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; is proud to be a pioneer in organizing experiential tours combined with soul healing, helping you not only travel but also find your true self through majestic nature.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Frequently asked questions about Lan Ha Bay&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;I can&#039;t swim &mdash; can I still kayak?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Absolutely! You must always wear a life jacket throughout the paddling. Kayaks are designed to be very balanced and hard to capsize, unless the waves are too large or you intentionally fool around.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;What medical precautions should I note for a combined tour?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;You should bring band-aids, antiseptic alcohol, and anti-allergy medicine. If you have cardiovascular or musculoskeletal conditions, please notify the tour operator in advance so they can adjust the itinerary accordingly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Can children take part in the trekking?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Children aged 6 and up who are in good health and love physical activity can fully participate. However, parents need to supervise closely and should choose shorter trekking routes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;How much cash should I bring?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;On the bay and in Viet Hai village, cash is mainly used because electronic banking services are not yet common. You should bring just enough cash to buy drinks or souvenirs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;How can I protect the environment when traveling?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Follow the principle of &quot;Take nothing but pictures, leave nothing but footprints.&quot; Absolutely do not litter into the bay or in the National Park.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/0000/1/2025/12/30/kinh-nghiem-kham-pha-vinh-lan-ha-bang-kayaking-ket-hop-trekking-1.jpeg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;900&quot; height=&quot;584&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
